726996f-a.text:
Jamaica Ave. (formerly Fulton Street, originally the Brooklyn and Jamaica Plank Road), east from Eew Gardens Road (left; formerly known as Newtown Road and also New Haven Ave.),,The Williamsburg and Jamaica Turnpike junctioned with Newtown Road at the Jamaica Plank Road. At the right foreground was Distler's Park. Note.in 1931, the toll-house, if standina would be in the middle of Jamaica Ave., between 137th and 138th Streets. Distler's Park was on the east side of Van Wyck Boulevard,
south from Jamaica Ave. to Eighty-ninth Ave.
About 1889.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

726969f-a.text:
Jamaica Ave., north side, at its intersection with Eew Garden Road (right) and Metropolitan Ave. (left), showing in the Apex, formed by the last two mentioned streets, the Maple Grove Hotel, of
which, J. Hauswicth was the proprietor in 1891.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
